absence /ˈæbsəns/

(absences) 

1. N-VAR Someone's absence from a place is the fact that they are not there. 缺席 

例： ...a bundle of letters which had arrived for me in my absence. …我不在的时候寄给我的一捆信。 

2. N-SING The absence of something from a place is the fact that it is not there or does not exist. 不存在 

例： The presence or absence of clouds can have an important impact on temperature. 云的有无对气温会产生重要影响。

